in some bar somewhere.

25:45.152 --> 25:46.545
A tiger's spots don't change,
right?

25:46.588 --> 25:48.285
Or whatever that saying is.Todd,

25:48.329 --> 25:49.765
as much as we might want to,

25:49.809 --> 25:52.463
we can't always save
our clients from themselves.

25:52.507 --> 25:54.291
So, I should just
give up on him?

25:54.335 --> 25:56.598
A lawyer doesn't give up
on their clients.

25:56.642 --> 25:58.687
They build the best defense
they can,

25:58.731 --> 26:01.168
even when they disappoint us.

26:01.211 --> 26:02.778
Now come on.

26:02.822 --> 26:04.475
We need to go talk
to Johnny about his boots.

26:04.519 --> 26:07.304
I mean, whatever, the boots.
Brian took off.

26:07.348 --> 26:08.654
He cut his ankle monitor
and ran.

26:08.697 --> 26:10.569
Does that sound
like an innocent person to you?

26:10.612 --> 26:12.701
Todd, you asked me
to take this case, and I did.

26:12.745 --> 26:14.398
And I am going
to see it through.

26:14.442 --> 26:16.139
Johnny and Danny deserve that.

26:16.183 --> 26:18.359
But Brian doesn't?

26:20.666 --> 26:22.624
I'm gonna find him.

26:22.668 --> 26:27.107
Or at least... I'm gonna look.

26:35.289 --> 26:37.073
[cheering, whistling]

26:37.117 --> 26:40.337
♪ So hot like a diamond bright,
no, I ain't got kryptonite ♪

26:40.381 --> 26:43.514
♪ Living in the fast lane,
speed of light ♪

26:43.558 --> 26:45.081
♪ I bring the bass,
I got the juice ♪

26:45.125 --> 26:46.822
♪ Yeah, I'm the boss,
I make the moves ♪

26:46.866 --> 26:48.650
♪ I bring the bass,
I got the juice ♪

26:48.694 --> 26:50.609
♪ I bring the boom.

26:55.657 --> 26:58.312
So, uh, Johnny,
you're a male entert...

26:58.355 --> 27:00.183
Uh, you're an adult...

27:00.227 --> 27:03.099
Uh... you're a stripper.

27:03.143 --> 27:04.448
[laughs]
Just at night.

27:04.492 --> 27:07.451
Oh.One paycheck ain't
cutting it anymore.

27:07.495 --> 27:09.192
Not with two mouths to feed.

27:09.236 --> 27:12.456
And-and this was
your only option?

27:12.500 --> 27:15.459
Don't judge. It's legal,
and the good Lord blessed me

27:15.503 --> 27:17.853
with a little bit of rhythm
and a cute ass.

27:17.897 --> 27:19.333
Oh.I'll do whatever I need to

27:19.376 --> 27:21.291
to take care of my family.

27:21.335 --> 27:25.208
I understand completely,
and I'm not judging.

27:25.252 --> 27:27.863
I mean, maybe
if I'd had the... body,

27:27.907 --> 27:31.432
I would have done the same thing
when my first husband died.

27:31.475 --> 27:33.260
You're a widow.

27:33.303 --> 27:35.479
How long?

27:35.523 --> 27:40.746
I wasa widow
for, um, 15 years.

27:40.789 --> 27:43.705
Eight. It's weird, isn't it?

27:43.749 --> 27:45.272
Raising kids by yourself

27:45.315 --> 27:49.145
when you thought you'd be
doing it together... forever?

27:49.189 --> 27:51.365
Yes. I-I never imagined

27:51.408 --> 27:53.410
I'd be having
that conversation here,

27:53.454 --> 27:56.892
but, um, yes, it is weird.

27:56.936 --> 27:58.459
[laughs]

27:58.502 --> 28:00.896
Um, aren't you cold?

28:00.940 --> 28:02.855
Hell no! I'm burning up!

28:02.898 --> 28:04.813
Dancing's a great workout.

28:04.857 --> 28:06.902
And you were here
the night of the robbery

28:06.946 --> 28:08.730
with your boots?

28:08.774 --> 28:12.168
Yup. And a number of my regular
clients could confirm that.

28:12.212 --> 28:15.432
But Brian has those same boots.

28:15.476 --> 28:19.610
I bought two pairs.
Sale at Walmart.

28:19.654 --> 28:22.265
I don't know
how to tell you this,

28:22.309 --> 28:25.660
but we were over at your house
earlier-- Todd and I--

28:25.704 --> 28:27.618
and-and the cops were there,

28:27.662 --> 28:29.664
and they were
looking for Brian.

28:29.708 --> 28:32.754
He's cut off his ankle bracelet
and fled.

28:32.798 --> 28:34.364
What?! Cops?!Yes.

28:34.408 --> 28:35.888
Where's Danny?Well, he's...

28:35.931 --> 28:37.280
Well, he's fine. Please.

28:37.324 --> 28:38.412
[high-pitched]:
No! Sit...

28:38.455 --> 28:39.718
back down, please.

28:39.761 --> 28:43.417
Um, Mrs. Garrison
is still watching him.

28:43.460 --> 28:45.201
I can't believe Brian

28:45.245 --> 28:46.899
would do something so stupid!

28:46.942 --> 28:50.641
Damn it. I love him
as if he's my own son,

28:50.685 --> 28:52.556
but he just keeps
breaking my heart.

28:52.600 --> 28:54.297
He needs to turn himself in,

28:54.341 --> 28:56.517
or he's going to end up
in prison, just like his father.

28:56.560 --> 28:58.780
His father isn't in prison.

28:58.824 --> 29:00.434
Not anymore.

29:00.477 --> 29:02.479
Ray got out about a year ago.

29:02.523 --> 29:04.960
He did? Does Brian know that?

29:05.004 --> 29:06.962
I didn't tell him.

29:07.006 --> 29:09.399
His dad is bad news.

29:09.443 --> 29:11.488
What was his father
in prison for?

29:11.532 --> 29:14.796
Burglary. Like father,
like son, huh?

29:14.840 --> 29:18.278
Ray worked as a heat
and air conditioning repairman,

29:18.321 --> 29:20.280
and he robbed a bunch
of his clients.

29:20.323 --> 29:23.674
Ah. And he lives in Portland?

29:23.718 --> 29:27.243
Lives in Salem.
Fat Bass Trailer Park.

29:27.287 --> 29:29.724
Court notified me
when he got out.

29:30.812 --> 29:34.555
There may still be
hope for Brian.

29:36.383 --> 29:38.341
Thank you very much.

29:38.385 --> 29:40.343
[shrieks] Okay.

29:40.387 --> 29:43.738
I'm... I'm so sorry.

29:43.782 --> 29:45.522
[knocking]

29:46.872 --> 29:49.700
Well, hello there.

29:49.744 --> 29:54.314
Ray McAtee? I'm here
about your son, Brian.

29:54.357 --> 29:55.489
Do you have a moment?

29:55.532 --> 29:57.491
Sure. Sure, come on in.

29:57.534 --> 29:59.406
Get you a beer.

30:03.889 --> 30:06.848
Well, um, I'm sorry
to disturb you,

30:06.892 --> 30:10.025
but, uh, I'm-I'm a friend
of your son, Brian's, and

30:10.069 --> 30:13.507
I was just wondering
if-if you've spoken to him

30:13.550 --> 30:15.639
since you were released
from prison?

30:15.683 --> 30:17.685
I'm sorry to say I haven't.

30:17.728 --> 30:18.904
Ah.

30:18.947 --> 30:20.383
Why, thank you.

30:20.427 --> 30:23.386
No, not since, uh,
he was growing his first

30:23.430 --> 30:26.955
chest hair and my jerk brother,

30:26.999 --> 30:29.436
Johnny, stole him from me.

30:29.479 --> 30:31.046
And-and how did he do that?

30:31.090 --> 30:34.615
He called social services,
said I was an unfit parent.

30:34.658 --> 30:36.704
Unfit, my ass.

30:36.747 --> 30:39.533
Now that you are a free man,

30:39.576 --> 30:41.840
how is it
that you support yourself?

30:41.883 --> 30:44.755
I do what I can to scrape by.

30:44.799 --> 30:47.410
Once I get my HVAC business
going again,

30:47.454 --> 30:49.456
I'll be stacking the cash.

30:49.499 --> 30:51.066
You had your own business?

30:51.110 --> 30:53.895
Yeah, before I got locked up,
I used to fix HVAC systems.

30:53.939 --> 30:56.898
I was damn good at it, too.

31:01.468 --> 31:04.775
Look, I'm just saying,
people are gossiping about Mom.

31:04.819 --> 31:06.603
Oh, no! Gossip!Shut up.

31:06.647 --> 31:09.041
And Chuck's mom just heard
some crazy thing

31:09.084 --> 31:11.391
about Harry being in a cult.

31:11.434 --> 31:12.914
And it wouldn't kill you
to take Mom

31:12.958 --> 31:15.699
to some symphony benefit

31:15.743 --> 31:17.788
nonsense gala thing
that she loves

31:17.832 --> 31:19.790
so she doesn't have
to go alone or miss it.

31:19.834 --> 31:23.533
Um, no. No thanks. I'd rather
eat glass, thank you very much.

31:23.577 --> 31:24.752
Really? You'd rather eat glass?

31:24.795 --> 31:26.058
That's a little overdramatic.Really?

31:26.101 --> 31:27.929
I think, if anything,
it's under-dramatic.

31:27.973 --> 31:29.670
Allison and I went to
the Philip Glass Symphony once.

31:29.713 --> 31:31.846
Lawrence and I wanted to go.
Did you enjoy it?

31:31.890 --> 31:33.587
Not really.I don't care about
supporting the symphony.

31:33.630 --> 31:34.805
But you're not going
to support the symphony.

31:34.849 --> 31:36.590
You're going to support Mom.

31:36.633 --> 31:37.939
I've had a really bad day,

31:37.983 --> 31:39.854
week, and two-year stretch,
so, no,

31:39.898 --> 31:42.465
I'm not going with Mom to face
off with her mortal frenemies

31:42.509 --> 31:43.858
in ball gowns while she lies

31:43.902 --> 31:45.816
about her whole life
being so wonderful.

31:45.860 --> 31:49.472
Wow. Sounds like you really did
have a bad day. What happened?

31:49.516 --> 31:50.691
Don't encourage him.

31:50.734 --> 31:52.736
Why, thank you
for asking, Chuck.

31:52.780 --> 31:55.391
I'm sure Allison remembers
Brian McAtee?

31:55.435 --> 31:57.045
Yeah, he used to come into
the mini mart where I worked

31:57.089 --> 31:59.700
in high school
and shoplift beer for his dad.

31:59.743 --> 32:01.093
And you let him do that?

32:01.136 --> 32:04.139
Yeah, I'm the bad guy
in this story, babe.

32:04.183 --> 32:05.662
What about him?

32:05.706 --> 32:06.968
Oh, he's just missing,
on the run,

32:07.012 --> 32:08.752
wanted by the police,
and most likely,

32:08.796 --> 32:10.493
guilty and going
to jail forever.

32:10.537 --> 32:12.887
And I've been looking for him
everywhere, and cannot find him.

32:12.931 --> 32:15.890
So it's been super, super fun.
It's like a really great,

32:15.934 --> 32:18.023
awful weight on my shoulders
that I'll never be free of.

32:18.066 --> 32:19.720
Hooray!
Can I have the meat, please?

32:19.763 --> 32:21.156
I don't want
to talk about this anymore.

32:21.200 --> 32:23.985
[door opens]MARGARET:
Todd? Todd, where are you?

32:24.029 --> 32:27.554
Ugh. I have been looking
everywhere for you.

32:27.597 --> 32:29.599
He's been right here
at dinner where you

32:29.643 --> 32:30.731
were supposed to be an hour
ago. I have left messages on
your voice machine. I...

32:30.774 --> 32:31.906
Look, I don't want
to hear it, okay?

32:31.950 --> 32:32.951
You were right about Brian,
all right?

32:32.994 --> 32:34.300
He's a big old loser.I know, but Todd, I hav

32:34.343 --> 32:35.518
to tell you something.He'll never have a house,

32:35.562 --> 32:36.911
he'll never have a normal life.But Todd...

32:36.955 --> 32:38.173
He'll never have a mudroom,
or a job

32:38.217 --> 32:39.174
that pays him six figures,
he'll never

32:39.218 --> 32:40.915
have a tie that you approve of.

32:40.959 --> 32:42.003
He's guilty, okay?Stop talking for five seconds,

32:42.047 --> 32:42.917
so I can...
No, Todd! No.

32:42.961 --> 32:45.050
Brian is innocent.

32:53.058 --> 32:55.712
Okay, so what are we doing here,
and what the hell is this?

32:55.756 --> 32:59.673
It's an HVAC, or an H-WHACK,
or I don't know. I don't know.

32:59.716 --> 33:03.198
Uh, it's the heating
and the air conditioning.

33:03.242 --> 33:06.506
And-and Brian's father told me
that he used to repair these.

33:06.549 --> 33:10.901
So, I looked up his record, and
turns out that he burglarized

33:10.945 --> 33:12.555
a bunch of businesses
that he serviced.

33:12.599 --> 33:14.905
Okay. Did he work
on this, here?

33:14.949 --> 33:17.038
I have no idea,
but my gut tells me

33:17.082 --> 33:19.127
that he broke
into this building,

33:19.171 --> 33:23.175
and this air... thing
helped him somehow.

33:23.218 --> 33:26.830
Huh. The pawn shop guy did say
his heating wasn't working.

33:26.874 --> 33:28.919
[gasps]
Yes. Good. Okay.

33:28.963 --> 33:30.573
Great. Get on up there!

33:30.617 --> 33:31.835
Get on up there?

33:31.879 --> 33:33.054
You shimmy up the side.

33:33.098 --> 33:34.795
What? What am I,
The Human Snake?

33:34.838 --> 33:38.059
Todd, he might have broken in
through that vent right there.

33:38.103 --> 33:40.061
So, go!All right. Uh, okay, look.

33:40.105 --> 33:43.151
Look, I'm gonna... Hang on.Yes. Oh.

33:43.195 --> 33:46.067
Good. Yes. Ladder. Smart.[mumbles]

33:46.111 --> 33:48.591
Okay. [groans]What? Oh, Todd, that's...

33:48.635 --> 33:50.245
You just stand there and
do nothing. I'll do everything.

33:50.289 --> 33:51.725
No, no, I'll help.
Just up here. Yes, up here.

33:51.768 --> 33:53.335
Just please help. I...

33:53.379 --> 33:55.859
Oh, good. That way.That's a real team
effort. Thanks, Mom.

33:55.903 --> 33:57.774
Appreciate it.Now be careful
you don't get a splinter,

33:57.818 --> 33:58.862
sweetheart.I got it.

33:58.906 --> 34:00.908
Yeah. That's it. Perfect.[groans]

34:02.127 --> 34:03.606
Good. Higher. Higher.

34:03.650 --> 34:05.913
All right.Yes. And now faster, faster.

34:05.956 --> 34:07.219
Hurry up. Go, go, go, go.

34:07.262 --> 34:08.916
And, uh, be careful.
Don't break your neck.

34:08.959 --> 34:11.136
Well, which is it? Go faster,
or don't break my neck?

34:11.179 --> 34:13.094
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.
Can you hold this, please?

34:13.138 --> 34:14.748
Steady me?Okay. Go ahead.

34:14.791 --> 34:17.055
Okay. [groans]

34:18.056 --> 34:19.796
Good.[groans]

34:19.840 --> 34:22.625
[sighs]
Nope.

34:22.669 --> 34:24.888
No way any adult human
could fit in here.

34:24.932 --> 34:27.239
It's-it's a small hole.

34:27.282 --> 34:28.979
Okay, well, now take
that cover thing off

34:29.023 --> 34:30.633
and reach
around inside.

34:30.677 --> 34:32.113
Okay.

34:32.157 --> 34:33.723
Good.

34:33.767 --> 34:34.985
Stick your head in.

34:35.029 --> 34:36.117
Stick my head in?

34:36.161 --> 34:38.119
Uh-huh.[sighs]

34:38.163 --> 34:39.773
Squeeze on in there!

34:39.816 --> 34:40.948
It's too small!

34:40.991 --> 34:42.297
I'm telling you,
there's nothing in here.

34:42.341 --> 34:44.299
Do I have
to do everything myself?

34:44.343 --> 34:46.127
The one little thing
that I asked you to do.

34:46.171 --> 34:47.781
No, no, no, no, no.
What are you doing?!

34:47.824 --> 34:49.174
I asked you to get in there.
That's what I asked you to do,

34:49.217 --> 34:50.305
is get in there.Do not climb up.

34:50.349 --> 34:52.002
This is not meant
for two people.

34:52.046 --> 34:53.134
And look inside
and look for evidence.

34:53.178 --> 34:54.309
That's what
I'm asking you to do.

34:54.353 --> 34:56.137
At least take my hand, please.Okay.

34:56.181 --> 34:57.747
Hold me. Hold me. Okay.I got you. I got you. Look.

34:57.791 --> 34:59.097
Okay.See for yourself.

34:59.140 --> 35:01.186
See? Nothing in there. What?[gasps]

35:01.229 --> 35:02.796
What is on your hand?

35:02.839 --> 35:05.320
I don't know. Toxic vent dust,

35:05.364 --> 35:06.843
orange asbestos.
Taste it.

35:06.887 --> 35:07.931
What?Taste it.

35:07.975 --> 35:10.325
No. Ew! It's...

35:10.369 --> 35:12.588
cheesy.

35:12.632 --> 35:14.895
Danny.Danny?

35:14.938 --> 35:18.072
Like Santa down the chimney.

35:19.291 --> 35:22.990
MARGARET:
So, let's talk about that night

35:23.033 --> 35:25.210
that you went for a ride
with Uncle Ray.

35:27.777 --> 35:29.562
You mean in Brian's car?

35:31.999 --> 35:33.870
Yes, sweetheart.

35:33.914 --> 35:37.352
In Brian's car.
Where did you go?

35:38.353 --> 35:43.053
If I tell you, Uncle Ray won't
play games with me anymore,

35:43.097 --> 35:45.230
and I like playing with him.

35:46.144 --> 35:49.712
You play games
with your Uncle Ray online?

35:51.366 --> 35:53.194
It's okay.

35:53.238 --> 35:55.327
Answer the question, Danny.

35:55.979 --> 35:58.939
We went
to help Uncle Ray's friend.

35:58.982 --> 36:01.159
What kind of help did he need?

36:01.202 --> 36:03.204
He locked himself
out of his store.Mm-hmm.

36:03.248 --> 36:06.207
So me and Uncle Ray needed
to get in the shop

36:06.251 --> 36:09.123
through the secret door
and bring him stuff.

36:09.167 --> 36:11.995
What, uh...
what kind of stuff?

36:12.039 --> 36:15.129
Money and coins, jewelry.

36:15.173 --> 36:18.088
As much as we could carry
without dropping.

36:18.132 --> 36:22.180
And where was that secret door
that led you down into the shop?

36:22.223 --> 36:24.399
In the back.

36:24.443 --> 36:26.096
It's small,

36:26.140 --> 36:27.402
but I went through the hole

36:27.446 --> 36:29.796
just like Uncle Ray taught me.

36:31.276 --> 36:33.060
It was pretty fun, I guess.

36:35.454 --> 36:37.064
[sighs]

36:37.717 --> 36:41.024
Is this because
Uncle Ray stole Brian's shoes?

36:41.068 --> 36:42.896
I told him he had

36:42.939 --> 36:45.028
to put them back.

36:45.072 --> 36:46.378
I'm sorry.

36:46.421 --> 36:50.817
Hey, it's okay, son.
It's okay. Come here.

36:52.340 --> 36:54.124
You didn't do
anything wrong.

36:55.300 --> 36:57.737
We have to find Brian.

36:58.955 --> 37:00.827
Did you call his new number?

37:01.828 --> 37:03.699
No.

37:05.005 --> 37:07.790
Well, what else was I gonna do?

37:07.834 --> 37:11.446
Not run. I was afraid you were
drunk somewhere in a ditch.

37:11.490 --> 37:14.449
Just... I didn't see a way out.

37:14.493 --> 37:17.191
It's... it's like I couldn't
handle the stress, man.

37:17.235 --> 37:19.280
Yeah, you definitely need
some better coping skills.

37:19.324 --> 37:21.413
And you got
to stay out of trouble.

37:21.456 --> 37:23.806
My mom's not always gonna
be around to bail you out

37:23.850 --> 37:26.983
and give you my ties.

37:27.027 --> 37:29.072
I'm gonna get
my act together.

37:29.116 --> 37:30.726
For real this time.Yeah.

37:30.770 --> 37:32.946
Gonna stop drinking.
I don't know.

37:32.989 --> 37:34.469
AA, group therapy.

37:34.513 --> 37:37.820
Maybe some
Anthony Robbins-like badge

37:37.864 --> 37:40.127
of personal achievement
kind of deal. [laughs]

37:40.170 --> 37:42.347
Whatever works.

37:43.043 --> 37:46.307
Hey, do you think
I could keep the tie?

37:48.091 --> 37:49.745
Considering
the recent developments,

37:49.789 --> 37:52.226
there's no reason to pursue
this matter any further.

37:52.270 --> 37:54.228
This case, along
with the violation

37:54.272 --> 37:56.274
of the terms
of the ankle monitor,

37:56.317 --> 37:59.277
is dismissed.[Brian and Margaret exhale]

38:03.063 --> 38:05.326
Thank you so much,
Mrs. Wright.

38:05.370 --> 38:07.241
How am I ever gonna repay you?

38:07.285 --> 38:09.504
Well, you could start
with no more trespassing.

38:09.548 --> 38:10.505
Gotcha.

38:10.549 --> 38:12.072
Be grateful for your uncle.

38:12.115 --> 38:13.421
On it.

38:13.465 --> 38:17.251
And Brian, I am... so sorry

38:17.295 --> 38:19.297
I didn't believe in you.

38:42.320 --> 38:44.234
Oh.Oh, hey.

38:44.278 --> 38:45.540
Hey. Hi.Hi.

38:45.584 --> 38:47.847
Your mom just texted me.
Brian's off the hook?

38:47.890 --> 38:51.154
Yes! Redeemed in the eyes
of society. For now.

38:51.198 --> 38:53.374
He'll be okay. For now.

38:53.418 --> 38:55.289
I can't believe
his own father was trying

38:55.333 --> 38:56.986
to frame him for a crime.

38:57.030 --> 38:58.466
Yeah, well, this is why
parenting is tricky,

38:58.510 --> 39:00.903
and why people shouldn't
have any more babies.

39:00.947 --> 39:03.906
No more babies.No! No more babies.

39:03.950 --> 39:05.299
Not for a while, no.

39:05.343 --> 39:07.083
I mean, why would you
want to bring a baby

39:07.127 --> 39:08.389
into the world right now?

39:08.433 --> 39:10.391
You're not having
a baby, are you?

39:10.435 --> 39:13.133
It's actually illegal
for you to be asking me that.

39:13.176 --> 39:15.178
Oh.But no, not yet.

39:15.222 --> 39:17.180
We are having a baby
in November.

39:17.224 --> 39:19.313
Huh?Of 2025.

39:19.357 --> 39:21.271
In three years.

39:21.315 --> 39:25.058
Oh. So, you have a plan,
like, a family plan?

39:25.101 --> 39:27.103
Yup, we have a plan.

39:27.147 --> 39:29.018
We?Yeah.

39:29.062 --> 39:31.064
I mean, without a plan,
how are we gonna frame this baby

39:31.107 --> 39:33.066
for a pawn shop heist?

39:33.109 --> 39:35.024
Right, well, try
to pull that off

39:35.068 --> 39:37.592
while it's still small enough
to crawl through a heating duct.

39:37.636 --> 39:40.160
I think they stay small
for a while.

39:40.203 --> 39:42.336
[elevator bell dings]

39:42.380 --> 39:44.991
Uh, anyway, gotta go.

39:45.034 --> 39:47.428
Sure.But, uh, congrats

39:47.472 --> 39:49.256
to "redeemed in the eyes
of society" Brian.

39:49.299 --> 39:50.866
Yeah.

39:50.910 --> 39:54.000
You-- not so much.

39:54.043 --> 39:57.003
Thanks. Thank you. Thanks a lot.

40:13.367 --> 40:15.456
Wow. You look great, Mom.

40:15.500 --> 40:19.982
Thanks. And Chuck's tux
almost fits you perfectly.

40:20.026 --> 40:21.375
Hmm.

40:21.419 --> 40:25.205
Are these for me?
These flowers

40:25.248 --> 40:28.991
that my neighbor, Mrs. Jackson,
threw in the trash last night?

40:29.035 --> 40:31.646
Well, they're still alive,
and they're new to you.

40:31.690 --> 40:34.475
Oh, uh, anything else
on that other matter?

40:34.519 --> 40:37.957
Mm-hmm. Mm-hmm.
Check this out.

40:39.567 --> 40:42.004
[laughing]:
Oh.

40:43.397 --> 40:45.443
Right now?

40:45.486 --> 40:48.054
[line ringing]

40:49.055 --> 40:54.190
Margaret! Oh, hello. Where are
you? Are you coming tonight?

40:54.234 --> 40:56.018
Hi, girls. Yes, of course.

40:56.062 --> 40:58.020
My date was late,
but he's just arrived.

40:58.064 --> 40:59.413
BOTH:
Date?

40:59.457 --> 41:00.936
What about Harry?Who is it?

41:00.980 --> 41:05.288
Oh, it's just a handsome
young man that I know.

41:05.332 --> 41:08.422
Harry and I... have split.

41:08.466 --> 41:11.033
But you knew that, didn't you?

41:11.077 --> 41:14.341
I mean, the way
you've been gossiping about me,

41:14.384 --> 41:17.300
all around town,
which is so unkind,

41:17.344 --> 41:19.215
and frankly, it's ill-advised.

41:19.259 --> 41:22.610
I mean, Desiree, how would
you feel if somebody found out

41:22.654 --> 41:26.048
that your husband
had been let go from a job

41:26.092 --> 41:27.659
because of
inappropriate behavior?

41:27.702 --> 41:29.095
Or...

41:29.138 --> 41:32.402
that you have been
having long lunches

41:32.446 --> 41:35.580
every afternoon
at The Heathman,

41:35.623 --> 41:37.320
oh, with Erica's husband?

41:37.364 --> 41:39.148
[laughs]TODD: Oh.

41:39.192 --> 41:41.324
See you at the gala, ladies!

41:41.368 --> 41:42.587
That was cold.

41:42.630 --> 41:45.590
[exhales] Ice-cold. Come.

41:45.633 --> 41:47.374
Wow.

41:47.417 --> 41:49.376
Ah.

41:49.419 --> 41:51.726
This is for you.

41:51.770 --> 41:54.120
Mm-hmm.

41:55.469 --> 41:58.385
It's your old copy
of Harriet the Spy.

41:58.428 --> 42:00.996
Wow! I didn't know
we still had this!

42:01.040 --> 42:03.303
Thank you. Thank you.

42:03.346 --> 42:05.523
Was this in one of my old boxes?

42:05.566 --> 42:08.438
Where are my boxes, by the way?

42:08.482 --> 42:11.746
You still have my stuff, right?

42:13.618 --> 42:15.271
You didn't throw my stuff away?

42:15.315 --> 42:17.447
Mom? It was only three boxes!

42:17.491 --> 42:20.755
It was four boxes.
